subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis:
Overall size between 2.4 and 
3.75 mm
; mandibles long (mandible length longer than the distance between the ventrolateral margins of the head, near the bases of the mandibles), sickle-shaped (
Fig. 17A
); antenna 15-segmented and filiform in females (
Fig. 17D
), 14-segmented in males; first male flagellomere not modified (
Fig. 20B
). Mesosoma higher than wide; pronotal shoulders angular (
Fig. 17C
); epomia well developed; presence of teeth, one on each scutellar bridge, near the posterolateral margin of the scutellar fovea, plus a small tooth in the middle posterior part of the scutellar disc (
Fig. 17E
). Forewing with closed radial cell (
Fig. 17F
).
